# {PROJECT_NAME} - Java Backend Development Rules

## Configuration Placeholders
**IMPORTANT**: Replace the following placeholders with your actual values:
- `{COMPANY_NAME}` - Your company name (e.g., "company", "acme", "myorg")
- `{PROJECT_NAME}` - Your project name (e.g., "KDS", "Video Transcoding Service")
- `{PROJECT_DESCRIPTION}` - Brief description of your project

## Project Overview
{PROJECT_NAME} is a microservices platform built with Spring Boot 3.3.x (Java 21), using MongoDB and PostgreSQL databases, with Liquibase for database migrations.

### Technology Stack
- **Java Version**: 21 (LTS)
- **Spring Boot Version**: 3.3.5 (or latest 3.3.x)
- **Maven Compiler**: Java 21 (source and target)
- **Databases**: MongoDB (secondary), PostgreSQL (primary)
- **Config Server**: Spring Cloud Config
- **Messaging**: Kafka for async events
- **PDF Generation**: iText 7.x
- **Mapping**: MapStruct (recommended), Dozer (legacy support)

---

## 1. PROJECT STRUCTURE

### 1.1 Parent-Child Hierarchy
```
java-parent/                          # Root parent POM
├── pom.xml                           # Master POM with all dependency versions
├── utility-libs/                     # Shared utility libraries
│   ├── exception-util-lib/           # CustomException base class
│   ├── common-util-lib/              # Common utilities
│   ├── report-lib/                   # PDF report generation
│   ├── kafka-lib/                    # Kafka utilities
│   ├── sms-lib/                      # SMS integration
│   ├── email-lib/                    # Email integration
│   ├── whatsapp-lib/                 # WhatsApp integration
│   └── ...
├── common-ms/                        # Common shared modules
│   ├── common-jar/                   # Common VOs and utilities
│   └── patient-case-common-model-jar/
└── {service-name}-ms/                # Microservices
    ├── pom.xml                       # Service parent POM
    ├── {service-name}-jar/           # Business logic, VOs, Exceptions
    ├── {service-name}-model-jar/     # Database models (optional)
    └── {service-name}-svc/           # REST API, Service, Repository
```

### 1.2 Microservice Module Structure
Each microservice follows this structure:
```
{service-name}-ms/
├── pom.xml                           # Parent POM for the MS
├── {service-name}-jar/               # Shared library JAR
│   ├── pom.xml
│   └── src/main/java/com/{COMPANY_NAME}/{service}/
│       ├── exception/                # Custom exceptions
│       └── vo/                       # Value Objects (DTOs)
├── {service-name}-model-jar/         # Database models (optional)
│   ├── pom.xml
│   └── src/main/java/com/{COMPANY_NAME}/{service}/model/
└── {service-name}-svc/               # Main service implementation
    ├── pom.xml
    └── src/main/
        ├── java/com/{COMPANY_NAME}/{service}/
        │   ├── {ServiceName}Application.java
        │   ├── controller/           # REST controllers
        │   ├── service/              # Business logic
        │   ├── repository/           # Data access
        │   ├── exception/            # Exception handlers
        │   ├── util/                 # Utilities, mappers
        │   └── kafka/utils/          # Kafka listeners (if needed)
        └── resources/
            ├── bootstrap.properties  # Config server settings
            ├── bootstrap-{env}.properties
            ├── logback-spring.xml
            └── db/                   # Liquibase (if using PostgreSQL)
```

---

## 2. POM FILE PATTERNS

### 2.1 Parent POM (java-parent/pom.xml)
- All dependency versions are centralized in `<properties>`
- Use version properties like `${spring-boot-version}`, `${lombok-version}`, `${java.version}`
- All internal library versions follow pattern: `${service-name-jar-version}`
- Example: `${patient-jar-version}`, `${cdr-jar-version}`
- **Recommended versions for Java 21**:
  ```xml
  <properties>
      <java.version>21</java.version>
      <maven.compiler.source>21</maven.compiler.source>
      <maven.compiler.target>21</maven.compiler.target>
      <spring-boot.version>3.3.5</spring-boot.version>
      <maven-compiler-plugin.version>3.11.0</maven-compiler-plugin.version>
      <lombok.version>1.18.30</lombok.version>
      <mapstruct.version>1.5.5.Final</mapstruct.version>
  </properties>
  ```

### 2.2 Service POM Dependencies
```xml
<!-- Always include for service JARs -->
<dependency>
    <groupId>com.{COMPANY_NAME}.{service}</groupId>
    <artifactId>{service}-jar</artifactId>
    <version>${{service}-jar-version}</version>
</dependency>

<!-- Auth is typically required -->
<dependency>
    <groupId>com.{COMPANY_NAME}.auth</groupId>
    <artifactId>auth-jar</artifactId>
    <version>${auth-jar-version}</version>
</dependency>

<!-- Common utilities -->
<dependency>
    <groupId>com.{COMPANY_NAME}.common.util</groupId>
    <artifactId>common-util-lib</artifactId>
    <version>${common-util-lib-version}</version>
</dependency>
```

### 2.3 Build Plugins (in -svc modules)
```xml
<properties>
    <java.version>21</java.version>
    <maven.compiler.source>21</maven.compiler.source>
    <maven.compiler.target>21</maven.compiler.target>
    <spring-boot.version>3.3.5</spring-boot.version>
</properties>

<build>
    <plugins>
        <!-- Maven Compiler Plugin - Java 21 -->
        <plugin>
            <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
            <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>
            <version>3.11.0</version>
            <configuration>
                <source>21</source>
                <target>21</target>
                <release>21</release>
                <annotationProcessorPaths>
                    <path>
                        <groupId>org.projectlombok</groupId>
                        <artifactId>lombok-mapstruct-binding</artifactId>
                        <version>${lombok-mapstruct-binding-version}</version>
                    </path>
                    <path>
                        <groupId>org.mapstruct</groupId>
                        <artifactId>mapstruct-processor</artifactId>
                        <version>${mapstruct-version}</version>
                    </path>
                    <path>
                        <groupId>org.projectlombok</groupId>
                        <artifactId>lombok</artifactId>
                        <version>${lombok-version}</version>
                    </path>
                </annotationProcessorPaths>
            </configuration>
        </plugin>
        
        <!-- Spring Boot -->
        <plugin>
            <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
            <artifactId>spring-boot-maven-plugin</artifactId>
            <version>${spring-boot.version}</version>
            <configuration>
                <mainClass>com.{COMPANY_NAME}.{service}.{ServiceName}Application</mainClass>
            </configuration>
        </plugin>
        
        <!-- Swagger generation -->
        <plugin>
            <groupId>com.github.kongchen</groupId>
            <artifactId>swagger-maven-plugin</artifactId>
            <version>${swagger-maven-plugin-version}</version>
        </plugin>
    </plugins>
</build>
```

