## 3. CONTROLLER PATTERN

### 3.1 Controller Interface (in controller/ folder)
```java
package com.{COMPANY_NAME}.{service}.controller;

/**
 * Interface defining REST endpoints for {Entity}.
 */
public interface {Entity}Controller {
    
    ResponseEntity<{Entity}VO> get{Entity}ById(String id) throws {Entity}NotFoundException;
    
    ResponseEntity<Page<{Entity}VO>> getAll{Entity}s(Pageable pageable);
    
    ResponseEntity<{Entity}VO> create{Entity}({Entity}VO vo) throws {Entity}Exception;
    
    ResponseEntity<{Entity}VO> update{Entity}({Entity}VO vo) 
        throws {Entity}NotFoundException, {Entity}Exception;
    
    ResponseEntity<Void> delete{Entity}(String id) throws {Entity}NotFoundException;
}
```

### 3.2 Controller Implementation
```java
package com.{COMPANY_NAME}.{service}.controller;

@RestController
@Api(value = "{Entity} Service APIs")
@RefreshScope
public class {Entity}ControllerImpl implements {Entity}Controller {

    @Autowired
    private {Entity}Service {entity}Service;

    @ApiOperation(value = "Get {Entity} by ID", response = {Entity}VO.class)
    @ApiResponses(value = {
        @ApiResponse(code = 200, message = "Successfully retrieved"),
        @ApiResponse(code = {errorCode}, message = "{Entity} not found")
    })
    @GetMapping(value = "/{id}")
    @Override
    public ResponseEntity<{Entity}VO> get{Entity}ById(
            @PathVariable("id") String id) throws {Entity}NotFoundException {
        return new ResponseEntity<>({entity}Service.get{Entity}ById(id), HttpStatus.OK);
    }

    @ApiOperation(value = "Create new {Entity}", response = {Entity}VO.class)
    @PostMapping(value = "/")
    @Override
    public ResponseEntity<{Entity}VO> create{Entity}(
            @RequestBody @Valid {Entity}VO vo) throws {Entity}Exception {
        return new ResponseEntity<>({entity}Service.create{Entity}(vo), HttpStatus.CREATED);
    }
}
```

### 3.3 API Annotations
- Always use `@ApiOperation`, `@ApiResponses`, `@ApiResponse`
- Use `@Valid` for request body validation
- Use `@PathVariable` with explicit name: `@PathVariable("id")`
- Use `@RequestParam` with defaults: `@RequestParam(value = "param", required = false, defaultValue = "value")`

