## 8. LIQUIBASE PATTERNS

### 8.1 Directory Structure
```
src/main/resources/db/
├── changelog.yaml                    # Main changelog
├── prod-changelog.yaml               # Production-specific
├── sql-scripts/                      # General scripts
│   └── YYYY-MM-DD/                   # Date-based folders
│       ├── 00-{description}.sql
│       ├── 01-{description}.sql
│       └── ...
└── env-specific-sql-scripts/
    ├── prod/YYYY-MM-DD/
    └── others/YYYY-MM-DD/
```

### 8.2 changelog.yaml
```yaml
databaseChangeLog:
- includeAll:
    path: classpath:db/sql-scripts
- includeAll:
    path: classpath:db/env-specific-sql-scripts/others
```

### 8.3 SQL Script Format
```sql
--liquibase formatted sql

--changeset {author}:{YYYY-MM-DD}-{description} failOnError:false
--preconditions onFail="MARK_RAN" onFailMessage="Table/Type already exists"
--precondition-sql-check expectedResult:0 SELECT count(*) FROM information_schema.tables WHERE table_schema = 'public' AND table_name = '{table_name}'
--comment: Description of what this changeset does

-- ENUM TYPE CREATION
CREATE TYPE public.{entity}_status AS ENUM ('ACTIVE', 'INACTIVE', 'DELETED');
COMMENT ON TYPE public.{entity}_status IS 'Status enum for {entity} table';

-- TABLE CREATION
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS public.{entity} (
    {entity}_id TEXT COLLATE pg_catalog."default" PRIMARY KEY,
    field_name TEXT COLLATE pg_catalog."default",
    status {entity}_status,
    extension JSONB,
    deleted BOOLEAN DEFAULT false,
    created_on TIMESTAMP WITHOUT TIME ZONE DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    created_by CHARACTER VARYING(50) COLLATE pg_catalog."default",
    last_modified_on TIMESTAMP WITHOUT TIME ZONE DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,
    last_modified_by CHARACTER VARYING(50) COLLATE pg_catalog."default"
);

COMMENT ON TABLE public.{entity} IS 'Description of {entity} table';

-- INDEX CREATION
--changeset {author}:{YYYY-MM-DD}-{entity}-indexes failOnError:false
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_{entity}_field ON public.{entity}(field_name);
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_{entity}_status ON public.{entity}(status);

-- COLUMN ALTER
--changeset {author}:{YYYY-MM-DD}-alter-{entity}-{column} failOnError:false
ALTER TABLE public.{entity} ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS new_column TEXT;
```

### 8.4 Naming Conventions
- File prefix: `00-`, `01-`, `02-` for execution order
- Changeset ID: `{author}:{YYYY-MM-DD}-{description}`
- Always use `failOnError:false` with preconditions
- Use `MARK_RAN` for idempotent scripts

